---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Research"
  description="Research publications and developing frameworks by Daniel Edmund Rochatka, spanning AI retrieval, information systems, persistent agents, and foundational physics."
>
  <section class="page-intro section-pad">
    <p class="eyebrow">Research</p>
    <h1>Ideas developed far enough to expose their assumptions.</h1>
    <p>Research here includes formal publications, architecture programs, and manuscripts still being tested. Published and developing work are kept visibly distinct.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="research-list section-pad rule-top">
    <article>
      <div class="research-index">01</div>
      <div>
        <p class="research-status">Published · 2026</p>
        <h2>Hierarchical Voting Retrieval-Augmented Generation</h2>
        <p>A retrieval architecture that uses hierarchical evidence selection and voting to improve traceability and answer quality across complex source sets.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.20472565">View on Zenodo <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div class="research-index">02</div>
      <div>
        <p class="research-status">Published · 2025</p>
        <h2>Vocarum</h2>
        <p>A framework for consensus journalism that preserves evidence, agreement, divergence, and interpretive lenses rather than compressing them into a single artificial narrative.</p>
        <a class="text-link" href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.16636108">View on Zenodo <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span></a>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div class="research-index">03</div>
      <div>
        <p class="research-status">Developing framework</p>
        <h2>AxiomMesh and Paradigm Revectorization</h2>
        <p>A persistent-agent architecture in which memory objects retain identity and provenance while model-specific representations can evolve across different latent geometries.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article>
      <div class="research-index">04</div>
      <div>
        <p class="research-status">Manuscript in development</p>
        <h2>Transformational Physics Framework</h2>
        <p>An attempt to formulate dynamics from transformations and their conservation, treating energy as an accounting consequence rather than the starting primitive.</p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
